			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=3923#p3923"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1453">Lupuss</a></strong> &raquo; Thu Apr 01, 2010 11:31 am </p>

			

			<div class="content">Thank you for your answer, sadly I can't seem to find this option (in LXPanel 0.5.5). If I go to Panel Settings =&gt; Appearance, I can chose an image for the taskbar (like make it transparent) but I don't have an option to follow the current theme (and indeed it doesn't).<br /><br />I'm running Debian squeeze, although I don't think it's relevant here.</div>

			

