	<div id="p3926" class="post bg1">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p3926">Re: Change taskbar appearance?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=3926#p3926"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=391">Marty Jack</a></strong> &raquo; Thu Apr 01, 2010 2:52 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Right click panel, Panel Settings / Appearance / System Theme, uncheck Custom Color<br />Right click taskbar plugin in an empty space , Task Bar Settings (or navigate there from Panel Settings / Panel Applets / select Taskbar / Edit) / uncheck Flat buttons<br /><br />This should get you a panel that completely follows the system theme.</div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile3926">
			<dt>
				<a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=391">Marty Jack</a>
