	<div id="p3929" class="post bg2">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p3929">Re: Change taskbar appearance?</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=3929#p3929"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1453">Lupuss</a></strong> &raquo; Thu Apr 01, 2010 4:50 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">I got confused, there are two types of themes :<br />- Themes available in the Openbox Conf. Manager, they basically change the windows' upper bar. <br />- Window themes available in the Appearance Settings, they're the one you can match the task bar with.<br /><br />I guess getting the task bar to match the Openbox theme isn't readily feasible.</div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile3929">
